metadata.description:
				The "Recovery console: Allow floppy copy and access to all drives and all folders" parameter enables the SET command in "Recovery Console" mode, permitting the configuration of system variables, such as:;
- AllowWildCards: Enables "Wild Cards" in some system commands (for example the DEL command).;
- AllowAllPaths: Enables access to all computer files and directories;
- AllowRemovableMedia - Allows files to be copied to removable media (e.g.: floppy disks);
- NoCopyPrompt: Whilst a file is being copied, it does not prompt the user to override an existing file;
This parameter should be kept disabled, as when these variables are set, total access to all disk files and directories is allowed, regardless of the ACLs defined in the file system.
